'''Sawada Otsuka Kofun''' (沢田大塚古墳) is a {{ill|Round tumulus|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Naka Ward, Okayama|ja|中区 (岡山市)|12=draft|12=draft}}, Okayama City, Okayama Prefecture. It is part of the {{ill|Misaoyama Kofun Group|ja|操山古墳群|12=draft|12=draft}} and is not Historic Site1 as a historic site.

== Overview ==
Located on the northern ridge of the Misaoyama massif, an independent hill range east of Okayama City's center, this tumulus has been known for its exposed burial chamber, which now houses a Buddhist statue.<ref name="OkayamaCity">[http://www.city.okayama.jp/museum/kofun3/04.html Sawada Otsuka Kofun] (Okayama City Museum, "Explore Okayama City's Historic Site").</ref>  

The tumulus is round in type, measuring 16 meters in diameter<ref name="OkayamaCity" /> (or 25 meters according to some sources<ref name="SawadaOtsuka1988" />). The burial chamber features a single-entrance passage grave (片袖式横穴式石室) opening westward. The chamber's burial goods are unknown.<ref name="SawadaOtsuka1988" /> The tomb is associated with the powerful {{ill|Kamitō Clan|ja|上道氏|12=draft|12=draft}}, whose influence spanned the eastern banks of the {{ill|Asahi River (Okayama)|ja|旭川 (岡山県)|12=draft|12=draft}}. The kofun's connection to {{ill|Hata temple ruins|ja|幡多廃寺塔跡|12=draft|12=draft}} (a Kamitō氏 clan temple) suggests a continuity of their lineage, similar to the {{ill|Tōjinzuka Kofun|ja|唐人塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} and its link to {{ill|Shōden Haiji Temple Ruins|ja|賞田廃寺|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref name="OkayamaCity" />

== burial Chamber ==
The burial chamber is a single-entrance passage grave with the following area:<ref name="OkayamaCity" />
* Total length: 11.4 meters  
* burial chamber: 4.8 meters long, 2.4 meters wide  
* Passage: 6.4 meters long, 1.7 meters wide  

The rear wall of the chamber comprises three large stacked stones.<ref name="OkayamaCity" /> Compared to the famed {{ill|Three Great Stone Chambers of Kibi|ja|吉備三大巨石墳|12=draft|12=draft}}—including {{ill|Kōmorizuka Kofun|ja|こうもり塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yata Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|箭田大塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Musa Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|牟佐大塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}—which utilize one or two stacked layers, this burial chamber predates them and represents a highly advanced design for its time.<ref name="OkayamaCity" />

<gallery>
File:Sawada Otsuka Kofun, genshitsu-1.jpg|Main chamber (rear wall side)
File:Sawada Otsuka Kofun, genshitsu-2.jpg|Main chamber (passage side)
File:Sawada Otsuka Kofun, sendou.jpg|Passage (leading to the chamber)
</gallery>

