* Total length: 11.4 meters  
* burial chamber: 4.8 meters long, 2.4 meters wide  
* Passage: 6.4 meters long, 1.7 meters wide  

The rear wall of the chamber comprises three large stacked stones.<ref name="OkayamaCity" /> Compared to the famed {{ill|Three Great Stone Chambers of Kibi|ja|吉備三大巨石墳|12=draft|12=draft}}—including {{ill|Kōmorizuka Kofun|ja|こうもり塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yata Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|箭田大塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Musa Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|牟佐大塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}—which utilize one or two stacked layers, this burial chamber predates them and represents a highly advanced design for its time.<ref name="OkayamaCity" />

