'''Sawada Otsuka Kofun''' (沢田大塚古墳) is a {{ill|Round tumulus|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Round tumulus|13=User:Immanuelle/Round Kofun|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} located in [[:en:Naka-ku, Okayama|Naka Ward, Okayama]], Okayama City, Okayama Prefecture. It is part of the {{ill|Misaoyama Kofun Group|ja|操山古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Misaoyama Kofun Group|qq=}} and is not Historic Site1 as a historic site.

== Overview ==
Located on the northern ridge of the Misaoyama massif, an independent hill range east of Okayama City's center, this tumulus has been known for its exposed burial chamber, which now houses a Buddhist statue.<ref name="OkayamaCity">[http://www.city.okayama.jp/museum/kofun3/04.html Sawada Otsuka Kofun] (Okayama City Museum, "Explore Okayama City's Historic Site").</ref>  

The tumulus is round in type, measuring 16 meters in diameter<ref name="OkayamaCity" /> (or 25 meters according to some sources<ref name="SawadaOtsuka1988" />). The burial chamber features a single-entrance passage grave (片袖式横穴式石室) opening westward. The chamber's burial goods are unknown.<ref name="SawadaOtsuka1988" /> The tomb is associated with the powerful {{ill|Kamitō Clan|ja|上道氏|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamitō Clan|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, whose influence spanned the eastern banks of the [[:en:Asahi River|Asahi River (Okayama)]]. The kofun's connection to [[:en:Hata temple ruins|Hata temple ruins]] (a Kamitō氏 clan temple) suggests a continuity of their lineage, similar to the {{ill|Tōjinzuka Kofun|ja|唐人塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōjinzuka Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and its link to {{ill|Shōden Haiji Temple Ruins|ja|賞田廃寺|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōden Haiji Temple Ruins|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.<ref name="OkayamaCity" />

== burial Chamber ==
The burial chamber is a single-entrance passage grave with the following area:<ref name="OkayamaCity" />
* Total length: 11.4 meters  
* burial chamber: 4.8 meters long, 2.4 meters wide  
* Passage: 6.4 meters long, 1.7 meters wide  

The rear wall of the chamber comprises three large stacked stones.<ref name="OkayamaCity" /> Compared to the famed {{ill|Three Great Stone Chambers of Kibi|ja|吉備三大巨石墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Three Great Stone Chambers of Kibi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}—including [[:en:Kōmorizuka Kofun|Kōmorizuka Kofun]], [[:en:Yata Ōtsuka Kofun|Yata Ōtsuka Kofun]], and [[:en:Musa Ōtsuka Kofun|Musa Ōtsuka Kofun]]—which utilize one or two stacked layers, this burial chamber predates them and represents a highly advanced design for its time.<ref name="OkayamaCity" />

<gallery>
File:Sawada Otsuka Kofun, genshitsu-1.jpg|Main chamber (rear wall side)
File:Sawada Otsuka Kofun, genshitsu-2.jpg|Main chamber (passage side)
File:Sawada Otsuka Kofun, sendou.jpg|Passage (leading to the chamber)
</gallery>

